// euler_circuit.gk — GK module
//
// Bijective permutation of [0, range) via PCG cycle-walking.
// Every input in [0, range) maps to a unique output in [0, range).
// Visiting every element exactly once: an Euler circuit through
// the value space.
//
// Inputs (inferred from unbound references):
//   position  — which element of the permutation (wire, u64)
//   range     — size of the permutation space (init constant)
//   seed      — PCG seed for reproducibility (init constant)
//   stream    — PCG stream index for independent permutations (init constant)
//
// Output:
//   value     — the permuted value in [0, range)
//
// The native cycle_walk node handles:
//   - Auto-selecting the smallest PCG state width ≥ range
//     (16-bit for range ≤ 65536, 32-bit for ≤ 4B, 64-bit otherwise)
//   - Rejection via cycle-walking: apply PCG, if ≥ range, apply
//     again to the result, until it lands in [0, range)
//   - Deterministic: same (position, range, seed, stream) always
//     gives the same output regardless of thread or access order
//
// Usage:
//   h := hash(cycle)
//   user_id := euler_circuit(h, range: 1000000, seed: 42, stream: 0)
//
// Multiple independent permutations over the same range:
//   perm_a := euler_circuit(h, range: 1000000, seed: 42, stream: 0)
//   perm_b := euler_circuit(h, range: 1000000, seed: 42, stream: 1)

value := cycle_walk(position, range, seed, stream)
